## About\par
\par
The carousel component is built using the [Embla Carousel](https://www.embla-carousel.com/) library.\par
\par
## Installation\par
\par
<CodeTabs>\par
\par
<TabsList>\par
  <TabsTrigger value="cli">Command</TabsTrigger>\par
  <TabsTrigger value="manual">Manual</TabsTrigger>\par
</TabsList>\par
\par
<TabsContent value="cli">\par
\par
```bash\par
npx shadcn@latest add carousel\par
```\par
\par
</TabsContent>\par
\par
<TabsContent value="manual">\par
\par
<Steps className="mb-0 pt-2">\par
\par
<Step>Install the following dependencies:</Step>\par
\par
```bash\par
npm install embla-carousel-react\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Copy and paste the following code into your project.</Step>\par
\par
<ComponentSource\par
  name="carousel"\par
  title="components/ui/carousel.tsx"\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
/>\par
\par
<Step>Update the import paths to match your project setup.</Step>\par
\par
</Steps>\par
\par
</TabsContent>\par
\par
</CodeTabs>\par
\par
## Usage\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
import \{\par
  Carousel,\par
  CarouselContent,\par
  CarouselItem,\par
  CarouselNext,\par
  CarouselPrevious,\par
\} from "@/components/ui/carousel"\par
```\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<Carousel>\par
  <CarouselContent>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
  <CarouselPrevious />\par
  <CarouselNext />\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
## Composition\par
\par
Use the following composition to build a `Carousel`:\par
\par
```text\par
Carousel\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  CarouselContent\par
\f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  CarouselItem\par
\f1\u9474?\f0    \f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  CarouselItem\par
\f1\u9500?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  CarouselPrevious\par
\f1\u9492?\u9472?\u9472?\f0  CarouselNext\par
```\par
\par
## Examples\par
\par
### Sizes\par
\par
To set the size of the items, you can use the `basis` utility class on the `<CarouselItem />`.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="radix-nova" name="carousel-size" />\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers \{4-6\}\par
// 33% of the carousel width.\par
<Carousel>\par
  <CarouselContent>\par
    <CarouselItem className="basis-1/3">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="basis-1/3">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="basis-1/3">...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers \{4-6\}\par
// 50% on small screens and 33% on larger screens.\par
<Carousel>\par
  <CarouselContent>\par
    <CarouselItem className="md:basis-1/2 lg:basis-1/3">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="md:basis-1/2 lg:basis-1/3">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="md:basis-1/2 lg:basis-1/3">...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
### Spacing\par
\par
To set the spacing between the items, we use a `pl-[VALUE]` utility on the `<CarouselItem />` and a negative `-ml-[VALUE]` on the `<CarouselContent />`.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview styleName="radix-nova" name="carousel-spacing" />\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers /-ml-4/ /pl-4/\par
<Carousel>\par
  <CarouselContent className="-ml-4">\par
    <CarouselItem className="pl-4">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="pl-4">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="pl-4">...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers /-ml-2/ /pl-2/ /md:-ml-4/ /md:pl-4/\par
<Carousel>\par
  <CarouselContent className="-ml-2 md:-ml-4">\par
    <CarouselItem className="pl-2 md:pl-4">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="pl-2 md:pl-4">...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem className="pl-2 md:pl-4">...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
### Orientation\par
\par
Use the `orientation` prop to set the orientation of the carousel.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="carousel-orientation"\par
  previewClassName="h-[32rem]"\par
/>\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers /vertical | horizontal/\par
<Carousel orientation="vertical | horizontal">\par
  <CarouselContent>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
## Options\par
\par
You can pass options to the carousel using the `opts` prop. See the [Embla Carousel docs](https://www.embla-carousel.com/api/options/) for more information.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers \{2-5\}\par
<Carousel\par
  opts=\{\{\par
    align: "start",\par
    loop: true,\par
  \}\}\par
>\par
  <CarouselContent>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
    <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
  </CarouselContent>\par
</Carousel>\par
```\par
\par
## API\par
\par
Use a state and the `setApi` props to get an instance of the carousel API.\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="carousel-api"\par
  previewClassName="sm:h-[32rem]"\par
/>\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers \{1,4,22\}\par
import \{ type CarouselApi \} from "@/components/ui/carousel"\par
\par
export function Example() \{\par
  const [api, setApi] = React.useState<CarouselApi>()\par
  const [current, setCurrent] = React.useState(0)\par
  const [count, setCount] = React.useState(0)\par
\par
  React.useEffect(() => \{\par
    if (!api) \{\par
      return\par
    \}\par
\par
    setCount(api.scrollSnapList().length)\par
    setCurrent(api.selectedScrollSnap() + 1)\par
\par
    api.on("select", () => \{\par
      setCurrent(api.selectedScrollSnap() + 1)\par
    \})\par
  \}, [api])\par
\par
  return (\par
    <Carousel setApi=\{setApi\}>\par
      <CarouselContent>\par
        <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
        <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
        <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
      </CarouselContent>\par
    </Carousel>\par
  )\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
## Events\par
\par
You can listen to events using the api instance from `setApi`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers \{1,4-14,16\}\par
import \{ type CarouselApi \} from "@/components/ui/carousel"\par
\par
export function Example() \{\par
  const [api, setApi] = React.useState<CarouselApi>()\par
\par
  React.useEffect(() => \{\par
    if (!api) \{\par
      return\par
    \}\par
\par
    api.on("select", () => \{\par
      // Do something on select.\par
    \})\par
  \}, [api])\par
\par
  return (\par
    <Carousel setApi=\{setApi\}>\par
      <CarouselContent>\par
        <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
        <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
        <CarouselItem>...</CarouselItem>\par
      </CarouselContent>\par
    </Carousel>\par
  )\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
See the [Embla Carousel docs](https://www.embla-carousel.com/api/events/) for more information on using events.\par
\par
## Plugins\par
\par
You can use the `plugins` prop to add plugins to the carousel.\par
\par
```ts showLineNumbers \{1,6-10\}\par
import Autoplay from "embla-carousel-autoplay"\par
\par
export function Example() \{\par
  return (\par
    <Carousel\par
      plugins=\{[\par
        Autoplay(\{\par
          delay: 2000,\par
        \}),\par
      ]\}\par
    >\par
      // ...\par
    </Carousel>\par
  )\par
\}\par
```\par
